import React, { useContext } from 'react'
import Modal from "react-bootstrap/Modal"
import { Button, Form } from "react-bootstrap"
import {Context} from "../../index";

const CreateUser = ({show, onHide}) => {
    const {user} = useContext(Context)

    const [nickname, setNickname] = useState()
    const addUser = () => {

    }

    return (
        <Modal 
        show={show} 
        onHide={onHide}>
        <Modal.Header closeButton>
          <Modal.Title>ADD Info Hero</Modal.Title>
        </Modal.Header>
        <Modal.Body>
            <Form>
            <Form.Control 
            className="mt-3"
                placeholder={"Lead the hero's nickname"}
                />
                 <Form.Control 
                 className="mt-3"
                placeholder={"Lead the hero's real name"}
                />
                 <Form.Control 
                 className="mt-3"
                placeholder={"Lead the hero's superpowers"}
                />
                 <Form.Control 
                 className="mt-3"
                placeholder={"Lead the hero's origin description"}
                />
                 <Form.Control 
                 className="mt-3"
                placeholder={"Lead the hero's catch phase"}
                />
                <Form.Control 
                className="mt-3"
                placeholder={"Loading an image"}
                type="file"
                />
            </Form>
        </Modal.Body>
        <Modal.Footer>
          <Button variant="outline-danger" onClick={onHide}>
            Close
          </Button>
          <Button variant="outline-success" onClick={addUser}>
            Save
          </Button>
        </Modal.Footer>
      </Modal>
    )
}

export default CreateUser
